    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-07-01T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-07-01T17:00:00-05:00" n="353"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d353">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">837.61351/3150: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Braden</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-07-01T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 1, 1942—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received July 2—12:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>489. For Walmsley. Department’s instruction no. 169, June 25. The Institute has
                    accepted without change Defense Supplies Corporation letter of June 25 relative
                    to the 10,000,000 gallons of blackstrap. Moreover, at the Embassy’s suggestion
                    both the Prime Minister and Hevia<note n="12" xml:id="d353fn12">Carlos Hevia,
                        Chairman of the Cuban Price Control Commission.</note> have signed the
                    acceptance. The letter will be returned by air mail tomorrow.</p>
                <p>All the officials concerned have expressed their sincere appreciation of our
                    Government’s cooperation in this matter. I hope appropriate instructions to
                    release the blackstrap will immediately be issued.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Braden</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
